The President of the United States issued a statement congratulating Lebanon on its Independence Day. He expressed his commitment to supporting Lebanon's sovereignty, independence, and national identity, and praised the country's government for its leadership in seeking peace and stability. The President also expressed support for the Special Tribunal for Lebanon and emphasized the importance of ending political assassinations in the country. He vowed to support Lebanon in remaining free from foreign interference, terrorism, and war, and called on all Lebanese to work together for a sovereign and independent Lebanon. The President highlighted Lebanon's multi-ethnic democratic system, which allows representation for all religious and ethnic backgrounds, and acknowledged the contributions of Lebanese-Americans to the United States. He concluded by wishing Lebanon a happy Independence Day.